description: A ripe avocado yields to gentle pressure when held in the palm of the hand and sqeezed. The fruit is no sweet, but distinctly and subtle flavored, whith smooth texture. The avocado is popular in vegetarian cuisine as a substitute for meats in  sandwiches and salads because of its high fat content
